 American films responded in multiple ways, sometimes directly reflecting these turbulent times, and sometimes indirectly couching history in traditional genres and stories. In American Cinema of the 2000s, essays from ten top film scholars examine such popular series as the groundbreaking Matrix films and the gripping adventures of former CIA covert operative Jason Bourne; new, offbeat films like Juno; and the resurgence of documentaries like Michael Moore's Fahrenheit 9/11. Each essay demonstrates the complex ways in which American culture and American cinema are bound together in subtle and challenging ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Mai 2020) 0aMotion picturesxHistoryx21st centuryxUnited States. 0aMotion picturesxPlots, themes, etcxUnited StatesxUnited States. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aAlter, Nora1 aBeckman, Karen1 aCorrigan, Timothy1 aCorrigan, Timothy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEverett, Anna1 aMorris, Nigel1 aPolan, Dana1 aRehak, Bob1 aSchatz, Thomas1 aSmith, Dina1 aWilliams, Linda Ruth1 aWillis, Sharon08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066331040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813553238423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813553238.jpg  a978-3-11-066331-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-068861-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK